reviews.review_text: One Piece at a Time Like the Johnny Cash song about his car assembled from random new parts, this show feels kind of put together on the fly.  Maybe that's why we get three consecutive openers to begin the show while the crack technical crew chases down the gremlins.  This is an excellent quality board (i'd say) of a less than excellent show.  Brent is playing very hard at times but can't come up with a lot of words.  Jerry bails him out by taking Hey Pocky Way into Aiko to end the first set - I don't recall hearing that combo before.  Rough start to the three day run at Shoreline but I look forward to the next two shows.  Sound is fine!

Brent is wasted Brent is wasted. LOL.... Saint of Circumstance is an interesting train wreck LOL.  The show is pretty bad overall and I have never gave a bad review...BUT i would still have love to have gone to this show.  Worth a listen just for the weirdness of it
